  "prompt": "What is the square root of 40 in radical form?",
  "response": "The square root of 40 can be simplified and expressed in radical form as follows:\n\n\\[\n\\sqrt{40} = \\sqrt{4 \\times 10} = \\sqrt{4} \\times \\sqrt{10} = 2\\sqrt{10}\n\\]\n\n**So, the square root of 40 in radical form is \\( 2\\sqrt{10} \\).**",
